A double hijacking.
At Gimpo Airport's control tower,

00:25:42.312 --> 00:25:45.190
air traffic controller Chae Jiseok
intercepted the transmission

00:25:45.274 --> 00:25:47.484
bound for Pyongyang
and redirected the plane south.

00:25:47.568 --> 00:25:50.654
Japan Airways 351, Runway 32, right.

00:25:50.737 --> 00:25:53.615
Roger, Runway 32, right.

00:25:53.699 --> 00:25:56.243
Good afternoon, Japan Airways 351.

00:25:56.326 --> 00:25:57.619
Continue approach.

00:25:58.996 --> 00:26:02.082
GIMPO AIRPORT, KOREA

00:26:02.166 --> 00:26:04.793
From this moment,
this is Pyongyang Airport!

00:26:05.878 --> 00:26:10.007
Once the hijackers exit the plane,
capture them all alive.

00:26:11.008 --> 00:26:15.012
If they resist,
you may open fire immediately.

00:26:17.139 --> 00:26:18.432
Without them realizing,

00:26:18.515 --> 00:26:19.683
the aircraft passed over Pyongyang,

00:26:19.766 --> 00:26:23.228
crossed the West Sea,
and finally landed at Gimpo Airport.

00:26:42.581 --> 00:26:45.792
They cobbled together
a crowd of locals, students, and soldiers

00:26:45.876 --> 00:26:48.295
disguised as a North Korean
welcoming committee.

00:26:51.715 --> 00:26:56.136
They even went so far as to hang
North Korean flags on the terminal,

00:26:56.220 --> 00:26:58.388
but the whole charade was clumsy at best.

00:27:02.351 --> 00:27:04.978
Sir, something's not right.

00:27:07.272 --> 00:27:08.273
Move!

00:27:14.780 --> 00:27:16.073
As expected,

00:27:16.156 --> 00:27:18.116
the Revolutionary Army
sensed something was wrong.

00:27:18.825 --> 00:27:21.620
Alas, the grand operation
they had planned…

00:27:23.497 --> 00:27:24.498
Hey!

00:27:27.334 --> 00:27:28.335
You!

00:27:30.504 --> 00:27:32.756
Here, Seoul?

00:27:34.341 --> 00:27:35.425
Yes!

00:27:36.301 --> 00:27:38.095
…ended in failure.

00:27:40.472 --> 00:27:41.682
Do you want me to kill you?

00:27:41.765 --> 00:27:42.891
What the hell is this?

00:27:44.768 --> 00:27:47.521
Why are we in South Korea?

00:27:47.604 --> 00:27:48.605
I don't know.

00:27:48.689 --> 00:27:51.233
You don't know? I'm going to kill you!

00:27:51.316 --> 00:27:54.111
If you kill the captain,
who's going to fly the plane?

00:27:57.406 --> 00:27:59.700
What about Pyongyang?
Not going there anymore?

00:28:04.204 --> 00:28:05.622
I'm going to kill you.

00:28:05.706 --> 00:28:07.708
All I did was try to help you.

00:28:09.251 --> 00:28:11.336
Will you make it to Pyongyang
if you kill me?

00:28:11.420 --> 00:28:14.297
Don't give me that crap.
I'm going to kill you right now.

00:28:14.381 --> 00:28:15.716
Calm down first.

00:28:16.800 --> 00:28:18.927
There's still a way
for you to get there safely.

00:28:19.011 --> 00:28:20.178
Shut up!

00:28:21.013 --> 00:28:24.057
I'm done falling for the words
of some Zainichi.

00:28:27.436 --> 00:28:29.229
You think I wouldn't notice?

00:28:30.605 --> 00:28:33.358
Zainichi like you reek, you know.

00:28:34.776 --> 00:28:37.446
That same stench you get
from pigs and dogs.

00:28:37.529 --> 00:28:38.572
Stop.

00:28:41.408 --> 00:28:43.326
There's a way for us to get to Pyongyang?

00:28:45.787 --> 00:28:47.122
You have my word.

00:28:49.374 --> 00:28:52.294
I'll get you to Pyongyang safely.

00:28:53.253 --> 00:28:55.338
Are you willing to bet your life on that?

00:28:57.049 --> 00:28:58.633
I'll bet my life on it.

00:28:59.926 --> 00:29:02.012
Japan,
closely monitoring the plane's movements,

00:29:02.095 --> 00:29:03.597
was thrown into complete chaos

00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:06.558
and dispatched a delegation
to South Korea to assess the situation.

00:29:06.641 --> 00:29:09.061
I don't know how
the plane ended up landing here.

00:29:09.144 --> 00:29:13.648
But now that it's in our country, there is
no way we're sending it to Pyongyang.

00:29:13.732 --> 00:29:15.942
"There's no way
we're sending it to Pyongyang."

00:29:17.319 --> 00:29:19.404
The mic. Mr. Jeong, the microphone switch.

00:29:19.488 --> 00:29:20.906
-What about it?
-The microphone.

00:29:20.989 --> 00:29:22.365
Right, sorry.

00:29:23.408 --> 00:29:27.120
Who'd want to send it
to Pyongyang? None of us wants that.

00:29:27.204 --> 00:29:29.081
"Who'd want to send it to Pyongyang?"

00:29:29.164 --> 00:29:30.624
But listen.

00:29:30.707 --> 00:29:33.001
With the passengers' lives at stake,

00:29:33.585 --> 00:29:36.797
we need to leave room for negotiation.

00:29:38.090 --> 00:29:40.258
So why did you let it
come here in the first place?

00:29:40.342 --> 00:29:42.094
This should've been handled in Japan!

00:29:42.177 --> 00:29:43.804
"It should've been handled in Japan."

00:29:43.887 --> 00:29:47.099
This really puts us
in a difficult position too,

00:29:47.599 --> 00:29:49.893
but the President's stance
is absolutely firm.

00:29:49.976 --> 00:29:51.937
"…is absolutely firm."

00:29:53.897 --> 00:29:56.316
We're well aware that public opinion

00:29:56.399 --> 00:29:57.776
in South Korea isn't favorable

00:29:57.859 --> 00:29:59.861
because of the recent hijacking incident.

00:29:59.945 --> 00:30:03.156
But there are more than a hundred lives
on the line here.

00:30:03.240 --> 00:30:07.494
So shouldn't we approach this
from a humanitarian perspective

00:30:07.577 --> 00:30:09.037
rather than a political one?

00:30:10.747 --> 00:30:12.999
Look, it's not public opinion
we're concerned about.

00:30:13.083 --> 00:30:15.585
Our priority is the safety
of the South Korean aircraft

00:30:15.669 --> 00:30:17.379
and citizens still held in the North.

00:30:17.462 --> 00:30:19.714
We're not saying
you can't negotiate with them.

00:30:19.798 --> 00:30:21.508
We're saying sending it to Pyongyang is

00:30:21.591 --> 00:30:23.593
- absolutely out of the question.
- That's right…

00:30:26.012 --> 00:30:28.140
- Geez, what…
- That's right.

00:30:28.223 --> 00:30:31.601
After all, if we don't start
the engines from outside,

00:30:31.685 --> 00:30:34.187
the plane can't even take off.

00:30:34.271 --> 00:30:36.398
They're not some miracle workers,
are they?

00:30:36.481 --> 00:30:39.985
In the end,
they'll have no choice but to give in.

00:30:40.068 --> 00:30:42.779
The South Korean government never admitted

00:30:42.863 --> 00:30:44.739
that it had deliberately
diverted the plane.

00:30:45.240 --> 00:30:47.742
On that plane
are our citizens.

00:30:47.826 --> 00:30:49.870
Japanese citizens.

00:30:51.163 --> 00:30:54.332
They're completely innocent people,
just like you.

00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:58.712
We fully understand the position
of the South Korean government.

00:30:58.795 --> 00:31:02.465
But right now, please put
the passengers' lives

00:31:02.549 --> 00:31:05.343
and safety above all else.

00:31:05.427 --> 00:31:08.597
I sincerely urge you.

00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:10.432
The gap between the two sides was clear,

00:31:10.515 --> 00:31:12.434
and there was little sign of compromise.

00:31:15.187 --> 00:31:18.815
This is Japan Airways 351.

