The engines have shut down,

00:31:23.612 --> 00:31:27.199
and all the power
and ventilation systems are down.

00:31:27.741 --> 00:31:31.036
Unless we get air
into the cabin immediately,

00:31:31.119 --> 00:31:33.163
it will be difficult to breathe.

00:31:34.122 --> 00:31:35.332
I repeat.

00:31:36.708 --> 00:31:38.835
We need air in the cabin.

00:31:39.586 --> 00:31:41.796
The engines have shut down…

00:31:41.880 --> 00:31:44.925
…and all the power
and ventilations are down.

00:31:45.592 --> 00:31:48.762
Unless we get air
into the cabin immediately,

00:31:48.845 --> 00:31:50.931
it will be difficult to breathe.

00:31:54.309 --> 00:31:55.936
This is Seoul Approach Control.

00:31:57.020 --> 00:31:58.188
Open the door.

00:31:58.855 --> 00:32:01.858
Once again, open the door.

00:32:03.360 --> 00:32:04.694
Like you said,

00:32:05.654 --> 00:32:08.865
we pinned all the blame
on the Japanese government.

00:32:09.491 --> 00:32:10.575
Good.

00:32:11.868 --> 00:32:15.872
The Japanese government is
probably trying to figure out a way

00:32:15.956 --> 00:32:19.125
to send you to Pyongyang
for the passengers' safety.

00:32:23.088 --> 00:32:25.090
The problem is
the South Korean government.

00:32:29.427 --> 00:32:31.721
They won't let you go that easily.

00:32:40.772 --> 00:32:41.773
I owe you one.

00:32:49.656 --> 00:32:51.199
So what's your plan?

00:32:52.784 --> 00:32:54.744
You need a justification.

00:33:00.292 --> 00:33:02.836
Let all the remaining passengers go.

00:33:02.919 --> 00:33:05.880
You bastard. You think
we're going to fall for that again?

00:33:10.135 --> 00:33:11.553
Hey.

00:33:12.387 --> 00:33:14.973
Who the hell are you, really?

00:33:15.557 --> 00:33:16.850
I told you.

00:33:17.434 --> 00:33:19.436
I'm a businessman.

00:33:20.061 --> 00:33:21.771
What are you playing at?

00:33:30.155 --> 00:33:33.408
All I want is to settle this quietly.

00:33:34.492 --> 00:33:36.286
Send you to Pyongyang

00:33:36.911 --> 00:33:38.663
and finish my business.

00:33:39.289 --> 00:33:41.624
We're not letting any more passengers go.

00:33:43.293 --> 00:33:46.379
If the South Korean government
doesn't accept our demands,

00:33:46.463 --> 00:33:48.548
we're killing them all!

00:33:48.631 --> 00:33:51.885
And of course,
we'll cut your head off first.

00:33:52.677 --> 00:33:53.762
Fine.

00:33:55.930 --> 00:33:58.016
Then let's do it another way.

00:33:59.809 --> 00:34:02.062
Bring me the briefcase I gave you.

00:34:02.645 --> 00:34:04.606
Inside is the answer

00:34:04.689 --> 00:34:07.525
to get you to Pyongyang.

00:35:56.801 --> 00:35:59.095
What was that?

00:35:59.596 --> 00:36:00.764
Was that a gunshot?

00:36:00.847 --> 00:36:03.141
What? We've got guns?

00:36:10.940 --> 00:36:12.358
Put the gun down now.

00:36:16.613 --> 00:36:17.947
Otherwise,

00:36:18.490 --> 00:36:19.824
we all die together.

00:36:21.826 --> 00:36:23.995
Go ahead.

00:36:28.792 --> 00:36:29.793
Come on, do it.

00:37:04.202 --> 00:37:06.079
They heard a gunshot
from inside the plane.

00:37:06.162 --> 00:37:07.997
They heard a gunshot
from inside the plane!

00:37:08.081 --> 00:37:09.332
A gunshot?

00:37:09.415 --> 00:37:11.459
-Good grief.
-Really?

00:37:12.794 --> 00:37:13.962
As you just saw,

00:37:15.713 --> 00:37:18.550
this isn't like the toys you're holding.

00:37:19.676 --> 00:37:21.594
This one can actually kill.

00:37:24.681 --> 00:37:25.682
So,

00:37:27.308 --> 00:37:28.852
what are you going to do to us?

00:37:29.352 --> 00:37:31.020
From now on,

00:37:31.104 --> 00:37:34.732
you're going to quietly follow
my orders and go to Pyongyang.

00:37:36.526 --> 00:37:37.527
That's right.

00:37:37.610 --> 00:37:40.655
They took the passengers
hostage to seize the plane.

00:37:40.738 --> 00:37:45.159
Now, I'll take them hostage
to get out of here.

00:37:45.243 --> 00:37:48.913
From here on,
tell them exactly what I'm about to say.

00:37:52.166 --> 00:37:53.960
We want…

00:37:54.836 --> 00:37:58.506
We want nothing more than that.

00:38:00.008 --> 00:38:03.303
"We want nothing more than that."

00:38:05.471 --> 00:38:06.973
If you don't meet our demands…

00:38:07.056 --> 00:38:09.309
"If you don't meet our demands…"

00:38:09.392 --> 00:38:10.435
…the second it hits noon…

00:38:10.518 --> 00:38:11.769
"…the second it hits noon…"

00:38:11.853 --> 00:38:14.480
…we'll detonate the bomb
on this plane and blow ourselves up.

00:38:14.564 --> 00:38:17.275
"…we'll detonate the bomb
on this plane and blow ourselves up."

00:38:17.358 --> 00:38:19.694
But if you do what we ask…

00:38:19.777 --> 00:38:21.821
"But if you do what we ask…"

00:38:22.322 --> 00:38:24.574
…we will safely release…

00:38:24.657 --> 00:38:26.075
"…we will safely release…"

00:38:26.159 --> 00:38:27.160
…all the passengers.

00:38:27.243 --> 00:38:28.328
"…all the passengers."

00:38:34.792 --> 00:38:35.793
Thank goodness.

00:38:36.461 --> 00:38:39.505
How can we trust them to keep their word?

00:38:40.298 --> 00:38:45.178
To show good faith, they said
they'd release half the passengers now.

00:38:45.720 --> 00:38:48.014
Fifty-eight in total.

00:38:50.350 --> 00:38:53.519
They're actually releasing the passengers?

00:38:54.228 --> 00:38:55.563
Hostage exchange.

00:38:55.647 --> 00:38:57.815
The condition I had Yamada deliver

00:38:57.899 --> 00:39:01.277
was that a senior Japanese government
official would take the place

00:39:01.361 --> 00:39:03.613
of the passengers
and become the hijackers' hostage.

00:39:04.322 --> 00:39:06.991
I was a Japanese businessman
who boarded the plane with drugs.

00:39:07.075 --> 00:39:09.494
To get out of the mess
without ending up in North Korea,

00:39:09.577 --> 00:39:11.579
I had to find a way to settle it.

00:39:13.122 --> 00:39:16.501
With a new hostage, the Revolutionary Army
secured their own safety,

00:39:17.126 --> 00:39:20.380
while South Korea's justification
for grounding the plane,

00:39:20.463 --> 00:39:23.341
citing passenger safety,
was no longer valid.

00:39:24.050 --> 00:39:27.011
North Korea granted
the Revolutionary Army asylum,

00:39:27.095 --> 00:39:28.805
and just as I expected,

00:39:28.888 --> 00:39:31.140
the plane was sent back to Japan
a few days later.

00:39:31.724 --> 00:39:35.395
They couldn't ignore the glare
of the international community.

00:39:36.145 --> 00:39:39.357
Once repatriated, Vice-Minister Natsume
and Captain Honda were celebrated

00:39:39.440 --> 00:39:43.528
as national heroes in Japan parlaying
that fame into politics and success.

00:39:45.405 --> 00:39:48.116
But Chae Jiseok, the controller
who diverted the plane

00:39:48.199 --> 00:39:50.910
and saved the passengers,
was never hailed as a hero.

00:39:50.994 --> 00:39:54.163
Instead, he was pressured into silence
about what happened that day,

00:39:54.247 --> 00:39:56.290
until he finally hung up
his uniform for good.

00:39:56.374 --> 00:39:57.375
That's right.

00:39:58.334 --> 00:40:02.588
That's how the President and the KCIA
keep this country running.

00:40:05.008 --> 00:40:07.552
- Here he comes!
- Hey, he's here!

00:40:08.761 --> 00:40:09.762
GIMPO INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT

00:40:09.846 --> 00:40:12.098
We share the joy
of the safe rescue

00:40:12.181 --> 00:40:14.726
of the abducted passengers in Seoul

00:40:14.809 --> 00:40:18.563
with the free people of the world.

00:40:19.522 --> 00:40:21.024
On this occasion,

00:40:21.107 --> 00:40:25.987
our government and our people have
once again renewed our vigilance

00:40:26.070 --> 00:40:28.614
against the atrocities
of the communist forces.

00:40:30.241 --> 00:40:34.120
After the incident,
Japan started airport security checks

00:40:34.203 --> 00:40:36.372
and even enacted an anti-hijacking law

00:40:38.082 --> 00:40:41.335
which meant the good old days
of casually boarding a plane

00:40:41.419 --> 00:40:43.880
with a briefcase full of drugs were over.

00:40:48.468 --> 00:40:52.513
Too bad about that briefcase,
but leaving it was the right call.

00:41:01.898 --> 00:41:03.024
It's a gift.

00:41:04.734 --> 00:41:06.819
I doubt we'll ever see
each other again, but…

00:41:10.948 --> 00:41:12.075
For your silence.

00:41:19.916 --> 00:41:23.169
ITAZUKE AIRPORT, FUKUOKA, JAPAN

00:41:25.046 --> 00:41:28.591
And so,
I arrived in Fukuoka later than planned.

00:41:29.383 --> 00:41:32.428
There'd been a bit of trouble,
but business is business.

00:41:35.139 --> 00:41:38.643
Finally, I was about
to meet my business partner, Ikeda Yuji.

00:41:39.727 --> 00:41:40.728
Is it a woman?

00:41:41.521 --> 00:41:42.522
It's a woman.

00:41:44.607 --> 00:41:47.777
I was told I had to go through her
to reach Chairman Ikeda,

00:41:47.860 --> 00:41:51.072
and the moment I fell out of her favor,
the deal was over.

00:42:07.213 --> 00:42:08.381
I'm Ikeda Yuji.

00:42:09.423 --> 00:42:10.675
I'm Matsuda Kenji.

00:42:12.885 --> 00:42:14.554
You're very late.

00:42:15.346 --> 00:42:17.431
Something came up.

00:42:19.892 --> 00:42:20.893
The goods?

00:42:26.274 --> 00:42:28.192
Can I borrow a light?

00:42:39.829 --> 00:42:42.415
I left the goods on the plane.

00:42:44.208 --> 00:42:46.335
I had to because of
the Revolutionary Army.

00:42:49.380 --> 00:42:52.091
Are you talking about the plane
that went to Pyongyang?

00:42:53.176 --> 00:42:55.553
That's the one. I was on it.

00:42:56.262 --> 00:42:57.763
I'm sorry.

00:42:58.764 --> 00:43:01.350
But I suppose
this is where our business ends.

00:43:02.351 --> 00:43:03.352
Farewell.

00:43:04.061 --> 00:43:05.104
It's a shame.

00:43:06.230 --> 00:43:09.025
I was hoping to show Chairman Ikeda
the best there is.

00:43:17.783 --> 00:43:18.868
I'll see you again.

00:43:53.194 --> 00:43:55.863
Damn it.
This hill's killing me.

00:43:55.947 --> 00:43:57.365
BUSAN DISTRICT
PROSECUTORS' OFFICE, KOREA

00:43:57.448 --> 00:43:59.951
It's killing me.

00:44:00.618 --> 00:44:02.370
After nerve-racking negotiations,

00:44:02.453 --> 00:44:05.122
Japan's Vice-Minister of Transport,
Natsume, boarded the plane

00:44:05.206 --> 00:44:06.874
-as a hostage himself…
-Wow.

00:44:06.958 --> 00:44:09.293
I thought they were
just a bunch of clueless idiots.

00:44:09.377 --> 00:44:10.920
But it looks like at least one of them

00:44:11.003 --> 00:44:13.381
- knew how to use his head.
- Yeah, pretty clever.

00:44:14.882 --> 00:44:16.050
Back to work, people.

00:44:16.133 --> 00:44:17.385
-Yes, Mr. Jang.
-Yes, sir.

00:44:17.468 --> 00:44:18.552
-Yes, sir.
-Come on.

00:44:24.225 --> 00:44:25.226
Oh, boy.

00:44:28.020 --> 00:44:29.939
- Mr. Kim.
- Yes?

00:44:30.523 --> 00:44:34.110
The Manjae Gang's movements
lately. Doesn't it bother you?

00:44:34.652 --> 00:44:35.653
Yeah.

00:44:36.862 --> 00:44:39.448
I mean, are these punks
trying to turn themselves

00:44:39.532 --> 00:44:41.909
-into export heroes by dealing meth?
-Right.

00:44:41.993 --> 00:44:44.245
Why do they keep getting involved
with the yakuza?

00:44:44.829 --> 00:44:46.580
- I know, right?
- Who is this?

00:44:48.666 --> 00:44:52.003
Uh… We still haven't been able
to identify him, sir.

00:45:02.138 --> 00:45:05.016
MEETING BETWEEN JO MANJAE
AND AN UNIDENTIFIED MALE IN A SUIT…

00:46:00.780 --> 00:46:02.114
Baek!

00:46:04.450 --> 00:46:05.618
Come here.

00:46:09.038 --> 00:46:11.665
Did you enjoy your vacation?
It must've been nice.

00:46:11.749 --> 00:46:14.085
You call a business trip a vacation?

00:46:16.962 --> 00:46:19.215
Where are you going? The boss is in there.

00:46:28.516 --> 00:46:31.060
Start talking! I said start talking! Hey!

00:46:34.271 --> 00:46:35.648
Move it, asshole! Hey!

00:46:39.693 --> 00:46:43.322
Talk, you bastard. Talk! I said, talk!

00:46:48.786 --> 00:46:52.540
Hey, come here, you bastard!
Spit it out! Spit it out now!

00:46:55.251 --> 00:46:56.419
You wanted to see me, sir?

00:46:56.502 --> 00:46:58.838
Hey, you're here.

00:46:58.921 --> 00:47:00.089
Good work out there.

00:47:02.842 --> 00:47:04.218
Let's go talk in my office.

00:47:05.553 --> 00:47:09.682
Hey! Start talking, you bastard!

00:47:11.809 --> 00:47:13.227
Get the hell up now!

00:47:38.377 --> 00:47:40.379
DIRECTOR GENERAL HWANG GUKPYEONG

00:47:43.674 --> 00:47:44.842
What've you got there?

00:47:46.051 --> 00:47:49.638
Uh, I got you some whiskey and cigars.

00:47:51.557 --> 00:47:52.850
Come on.

00:47:53.684 --> 00:47:54.977
You didn't have to.

00:48:05.905 --> 00:48:08.657
Damn it. It got on me.

00:48:11.785 --> 00:48:13.162
Hey, I liked it.

00:48:13.746 --> 00:48:16.582
The double hijacking. Good idea.

00:48:17.666 --> 00:48:19.001
Thank you, sir.

00:48:19.084 --> 00:48:23.130
The higher-ups can't stop raving about it.

00:48:23.214 --> 00:48:24.798
351 DOUBLE HIJACKING GIMPO
BAEK KITAE

00:48:24.882 --> 00:48:27.176
DHJ, double hijacking.

00:48:27.259 --> 00:48:29.553
JAY351 REQUESTING
DOUBLE HIJACKING AT GIMPO AIRPORT

00:48:29.637 --> 00:48:31.388
My code number, B73.

00:48:36.143 --> 00:48:39.563
I had given the boy's mother
the KCIA emergency number.

00:48:40.064 --> 00:48:42.441
"3, 8, 1, 1, 7, 7…"

00:48:42.525 --> 00:48:46.487
And thankfully,
she stayed calm and made the call.

00:48:46.570 --> 00:48:48.822
6, 7, 1, B, 7, 3…

00:48:48.906 --> 00:48:53.327
The KCIA
moved quickly, and just as I had planned…

00:48:53.410 --> 00:48:56.914
the plane bound for Pyongyang
landed at Gimpo Airport.

00:48:56.997 --> 00:48:58.916
Anyway…

00:48:59.416 --> 00:49:00.834
…about Jo Manjae.

00:49:01.835 --> 00:49:04.338
I hear he's been dealing meth
with the yakuza.

00:49:05.673 --> 00:49:07.007
Yes, I'm aware.

00:49:10.094 --> 00:49:11.303
You're aware?

00:49:12.846 --> 00:49:13.847
Yes, sir.

00:49:21.438 --> 00:49:23.691
So why didn't you report it to me?

00:49:24.358 --> 00:49:25.526
Mr. Baek?

00:49:27.278 --> 00:49:28.362
Baek Kitae.

00:49:35.869 --> 00:49:36.870
That's right.

00:49:37.413 --> 00:49:38.872
My name is Baek Kitae.

00:49:39.540 --> 00:49:42.459
Head of the Intelligence Department,
KCIA Busan Branch.

00:52:18.323 --> 00:52:20.325
Translated by Yoonjung Song